17_7	0.10215848	But recently their urgings have been taken more seriously, experts and historians say, because the South's political, social and legal climate has changed significantly since the era of the killings.
17_8	0.098856173	Blacks have steadily gained political power and have pushed for these cases to be heard before today's racially diverse juries.
17_9	0.079748179	At the same time, more witnesses, perhaps with less fear of retaliation and with heavy consciences they want to unburden, are coming forward.
